Former president Jacob Zuma's corruption trial will be back in the headlines once again on Monday. The High Court in Pietermaritzburg will hear a bid for leave to appeal Judge Koen's October decision. eNCA's Siphamandla Goge has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma's corruption trial will be back in the headlines once again on Monday. The High Court in Pietermaritzburg will hear a bid for leave to appeal Judge Koen's October decision. READ: NPA concerned about timing of Zuma charges against Billy Downer The judge dismissed Zuma's application for the recusal of prosecutor Billy Downer. The former president's legal team believes Downer lacks the title to prosecute Zuma.